Git init : To initialize the git in the working repo
Git add : Moving the changes from working repo to staging area
Git Commit : Moving the changes from staging area to local repo

Git clone
Git pull
Git push


To clone any remote repo we have 3 options: 
1) By using SSH
2) By using HTTPS
3) By using Git CLI    

we can clone any public repo by using https
only private repo use SSH

Note: 
-- If you clone any public repo we cant push your changes into the remote repo
-- If you want to push your changes into remote repo we have 2 options
     1) By using SSH
     2) By using Token

We have to add your public pem file into Git

To check pem file default folder is .ssh(c/users/.shh/authentication key

To generate new pem files keys: ssh -keygen
